# Log Explorer — endpoint smoke tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Health
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GET /logs/:id/meta
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Apache — meta (total lines, time range, file size)
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/meta

###

### Unknown log id — expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/does-not-exist/meta


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GET /logs/:id/chunk?cursor&limit
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### First page — start of file (cursor = first indexed line_no)
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=1&limit=10

###

### Cursor-chain — pass the nextCursor from the previous response
# Replace the cursor value with the `nextCursor` you got above.
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=11&limit=10

###

### Mid-file seek — proves the index is used, not a full scan
# This should be just as fast as the first-page request.
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=26000&limit=50

###

### Large page — maximum allowed limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=1&limit=1000

###

### Near end of file — last page returns fewer lines, nextCursor = null
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=56470&limit=100

###

### Bad cursor format — expect 400
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=not-a-number&limit=10

###

### Cursor not in index (skipped line) — expect 404
# Lines that didn't match the Apache log pattern were not indexed.
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=99999&limit=10

###

### limit out of range — expect 400 (limit > 1000)
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs/apache/chunk?cursor=1&limit=9999
